                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Revelations, Book 3</title>
                                <rubric>Incipit liber tertius Celestium reuelacionum domine Brigitte de Swecia monicio et informacio ad episcopum de modo tenendo in victu et vestito et oracione et qualiter se debet habere in mensa et post mensam et hoc idem de dormicione et qualiter in omnibus exerceat officium episcopale</rubric>
                                <incipit>IHesus christus deus et homo qui venit ad terram assumere humanitatem</incipit>
                                <explicit defective="true">Et nisi cauerit sibi</explicit>
                                <note>
                                    <p>The rubricator has marked the <quote>addicio </quote>at the end of chapter 10 as <quote>Capitulum XI</quote> (<locus from="60r" to="60r" scheme="folios"/>), so from hereon, the chapter numbers are out of sync with the text.</p>
                                    <p>At 31, 1 (<locus from="72vb" to="72vb" scheme="folios"/>) the rest of the text of the chapter is omitted and a reference to Rev. 8:23 given instead.</p>
                                    <p>Due to a leaf missing, the text breaks off at the middle of chapter 33, 5 (<locus from="72vb" to="72vb" scheme="folios"/>).</p>
                                </note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107145">Jönsson (1998)</title>
                                    <citedRange from="84" to="188" unit="page"/>
